name: Wave 3B — tool-backed relation via a description
description: ```
A tool-backed relation (`Mentioning is read via the link tool.`) cannot be
tested inline, but its related set can be materialised through a description
(`the pages that mention the entity`). The fetch is hoisted to a single prelude
`invoke` before the bind, and the description reads the bound result.
```
tags: inform7, wave3, verbs, relations, codegen

vocab_inline rel: ```
=== vocabulary ===
A page is a kind of thing.
An entity is a kind of thing.
Mentioning relates various pages to various entities.
Mentioning is read via the link tool.
The verb to mention (it mentions, it is mentioned) means the mentioning relation.

=== tools ===

Link
====
~ link(entity: String) : List
```

source_inline: ```
---
name: mentions
parameters: entity
vocabulary: rel.merconfig
---

To find mentions for an entity:
  let mentioned be the pages that mention the entity.
  complete with reason "ok".
```

expect_compile: pass
expect_no_unresolved:
expect_workflow_count: 1
expect_workflow_named: FindMentions
expect_invoke_tool: link
expect_swift_contains: state.bind("mentioned"
